â€œWhen a cure is no longer possible, the Death With Dignity Act adds another option for patients dying from a terminal illness. The prescribed medication gives patients peace of mind that they can use to take control of their dying if suffering becomes intolerable,â€ said Dr. Tom Preston, MD, a cardiologist and C&amp;Câ€™s medical director, â€œMost dying patients experience suffering. The Death With Dignity Act allows a physician to help his patients maintain as much control and dignity as they can at the end of life. Last night, the Death With Dignity Act provided a way to honor this patientâ€™s final decision.â€</font></strong></p><p><strong><font size="3">Note the clever use of language.&#160; Apparently, the public is supposed to buy into the argument that it is better to know you are going to take your own life so that your â€œpeace of mindâ€ is restored.&#160; While I am not sure how that equates with oneâ€™s eternal happiness, it is obvious that the twisted logic of these proponents of death knows no bounds.<br /><br />
